issueDTO.description:
### Context:

Add tier management to the reputation contract and integrate it with the NFT contract. This will enable the reputation contract to update NFT tier information when a user???s score reaches certain thresholds.

### Acceptance Criteria:

- Implement tier calculation based on point thresholds.
- Create integration with the NFT contract for tier updates.
- Build batch processing for efficient updates.
- Add events for tier changes.
- Implement unit tests for tier management.

### Development Notes:

This issue builds upon the reputation contract from Issue #441, #442 and #443:

```rust
pub struct ReputationTierContract {
    // Base reputation functionality
    reputation: ReputationContract,

    // Tier-specific additions
    thresholds: Map<TierLevel, u32>,
    nft_contract_address: Address,
    nft_client: NFTContractClient,
}

impl ReputationContractTrait for ReputationTierContract {
    // Delegate basic operations to base contract
    fn update_score(
        &mut self, 
        env: &Env, 
        user_id: Address, 
        new_points: u32,
        new_streak: u8
    ) -> Result<(), Error> {
        // Call base implementation first
        self.reputation.update_score(env, user_id, new_points, new_streak)?;

        // Calculate tier based on points
        let old_tier = self.get_user_tier(env, user_id)?;
        let new_tier = self.calculate_tier(new_points);

        // If tier changed, update NFT
        if old_tier != new_tier {
            // Find user's NFT token_id
            let token_id = self.get_user_token_id(env, user_id)?;

            // Update NFT tier via client
            self.nft_client.update_tier(token_id, new_tier)?;

            // Emit tier change event
            self.reputation.event_emitter.emit(
                env,
                "TierChanged",
                vec![
                    &user_id.to_string(),
                    &old_tier.to_string(),
                    &new_tier.to_string(),
                    &new_points.to_string()
                ]
            );
        }

        Ok(())
    }

    fn get_user_tier(&self, env: &Env, user_id: Address) -> Result<TierLevel, Error> {
        let score = self.reputation.get_score(env, user_id)?;
        Ok(self.calculate_tier(score))
    }

    // Additional implementations...

    fn calculate_tier(&self, points: u32) -> TierLevel {
        if points >= self.thresholds.get(TierLevel::Diamond).unwrap() {
            return TierLevel::Diamond;
        } else if points >= self.thresholds.get(TierLevel::Gold).unwrap() {
            return TierLevel::Gold;
        } else if points >= self.thresholds.get(TierLevel::Silver).unwrap() {
            return TierLevel::Silver;
        } else {
            return TierLevel::Bronze;
        }
    }
}
```

### Related Issues:

- Dependencies: #444, #445.
- Dependents: Reputation Synchronization Service issue.

